Example (illustrative), ML: "Long-document question answering degrades when the answer spans distant passages; retrieval-then-read pipelines drop the cross-passage link. We add a re-linking step before reading; success is +5 exact-match points on multi-hop questions with no loss on single-hop."

Example (illustrative), wet-lab: "Our assay's readout drifts across plates, confounding dose-response fits. We add a per-plate control normalization; success is a 2x reduction in inter-plate variance of the control wells without shifting the fitted EC50."

