The durable lessons that survive across {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}}s. Add a row whenever a {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}} produces a conclusion you do not want to relearn. A lesson belongs here (not in a backlog note) when it would change how you design the next {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} regardless of which component it touches. The rows below are illustrative.

| Lesson | Why it holds | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| Fix one component per {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} (illustrative) | Changing two at once makes the metric delta unattributable | First {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} where a paired change hid a regression |
| Always log the random seed (illustrative) | Run-to-run noise was mistaken for a real effect until seeds were pinned | A "gain" that vanished on re-run with a fixed seed |

